  planner_response {
    thinking: "**Defining the Core Theme**\n\nI\'ve zeroed in on the initial objective: crafting Shanmugaraj\'s portfolio. The plan is a dark, space-themed site; thinking through how to translate that to design. The existing color palette is a great starting point for the design\'s foundation.\n\n\n**Refining the Aesthetic**\n\nI\'m now diving into the specifics of the UI. I\'m aiming for a minimalist, professional design with animated stars and particles. It should evoke a GitHub and Linux terminal feel, leaning towards an ethical hacker and AI engineer aesthetic. I have a solid color scheme in mind and defined typography: JetBrains Mono for headings, Inter for body text. I\'ve also outlined the Hero section and core sections.\n\n\n**Outlining Project Details**\n\nI\'m now focusing on the project\'s nitty-gritty: design elements. I\'ve broken down projects into glassmorphism dark cards with a GitHub-style layout and terminal-like previews. For the background, I plan slow-moving stars with a soft grid overlay and minimal glow, while buttons will be rounded with a green glow-hover. I\'m also planning a minimal, transparent navbar with a blur effect. The desired overall look is professional and recruiter-friendly, echoing a GitHub dark UI and a modern AI startup.\n\n\n**Planning the Project\'s Structure**\n\nI\'m currently structuring the portfolio\'s components for efficient development. I\'m focusing on creating reusable elements: `ParticlesBackground` for the visual elements, `TypingEffect` for the terminal-style text, and a `Section` wrapper for smooth scroll entrances. This will be followed by dedicated components for each section like `Navbar`, `Hero`, `About`, `Skills`, `Projects`, `Philosophy`, and `Contact`. I\'ve also outlined a step-by-step implementation plan, starting with global CSS modifications.\n\n\n**Developing the Core Sections**\n\nI\'m now fully immersed in coding the main sections. I\'m focusing on the `About` and `Philosophy` sections first, infusing them with terminal-inspired design and clean typography. Next, I\'ll build the `Skills` section, which I\'m envisioning as terminal-like grid cards with hover glow effects. Then, I\'ll move on to the `Projects` section, where I\'ll create the glassmorphism and GitHub-style cards. Finally, I will assemble everything in `App.tsx` with responsive design.\n\n\n**Implementing the Design System**\n\nI\'m now establishing the design system\'s foundation. I\'ve defined color variables: deep-green, accent-red, soft-white, and muted-gray. I\'ve added a dark background and white text with a grid pattern. I also implemented glow effects with a neon green glow. For the background, I am considering a static CSS approach with an SVG or random div components. I\'m building a simple typing effect component next.\n\n\n**Simplifying the Text Reveal**\n\nI\'m now simplifying the text effect and exploring alternate animation techniques. A staggered reveal might be better, or using simple state updates with timeouts. I\'m working on a custom hook for this. I\'ve also detailed the skills UI with skill chips, cards with borders, and hover effects. I\'ve mocked up project data, including \"Sentinel,\" \"Nexus,\" and \"Orbit,\" alongside the associated technologies. Finally, the Philosophy section\'s content is being refined around security, open source, and minimalism.\n\n\n**Defining the Hero Image**\n\nI\'m now focusing on the hero section\'s visual appeal. Considering placeholder options for the hero image, I\'m leaning toward a minimal avatar generated by DiceBear to keep it sleek, using `https://api.dicebear.com/9.x/micah/svg?seed=Shanmugaraj&backgroundColor=050505` if styled well, or a stylish techy placeholder from Unsplash. I\'ll make sure it fits the dark UI.\n\n\n**Crafting the Hero Image**\n\nI\'m now zeroing in on the hero avatar. I\'ve scrapped the placeholder image idea and decided on a custom component: a glowing neon-green \"SR\" inside a ring. This should convey a professional and techy impression within the dark UI, in line with the established design aesthetic. I am ready to generate components.\n\n\n**Constructing the App Layout**\n\nI am now focusing on the app\'s overall structure and component integration. I\'m building out `App.tsx`, integrating the `Navbar`, `Hero`, `About`, and future sections. I\'m ensuring everything flows seamlessly within a dark theme, considering `Background` and terminal-style `Typing` components. The focus is on implementing a sequence-typing effect in the `Hero` section to display a series of lines.\n\n\n**Refining the Text Animation**\n\nI\'m now iterating on the hero text. I\'ve opted for a multi-line, sequential reveal effect within the terminal design. I\'m focusing on the Tailwind classes now, specifically `bg-matte`, `text-neon`, and `border-muted-gray/20` for a tailored aesthetic. I\'ve finalized a CSS-only stars animation with the DOM, inside a React.memo component. I\'m keeping the design minimal: radial green glow and faint grid.\n\n\n**Developing Core Components**\n\nI\'m now deep in component construction, specifically targeting the `Hero`, `Skills`, and `Projects` sections. For the hero, I\'ve styled a circular avatar with a neon ring and a shadow effect. I\'m focusing on text styling: JetBrains Mono for the name, and other styles from the established design system. I\'m building skill cards with glowing hover effects, aiming to visually represent technologies like terminals, servers, and AI with Lucide icons. My final focus is creating GitHub-inspired project cards with simple, non-RGB window borders.\n\n\n**Refining the Contact Section**\n\nI am now focusing on the contact section. I have decided on a simple form or mailto link. I am planning a call-to-action button, \"Initiate Handshake\". I will be using the terminal-style elements, maintaining the clean aesthetic.\n\n\n"
    thinking_duration {
      seconds: 29
      nanos: 382725653
    }
    stop_reason: STOP_REASON_STOP_PATTERN
  }
}
